		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Estlib wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><img src="http://i.imgur.com/bxdiszd.png" alt="Image" /><img src="http://i.imgur.com/xemNNTf.png" alt="Image" /><br /><br /><img src="http://i.imgur.com/McEKBIk.png" alt="Image" /><img src="http://i.imgur.com/5NCM5TW.png" alt="Image" /></div><br />Yeah, the overall feel is there, and there are many nice things about these images, but you really can't go &quot;fuck it&quot; and ignore those gigantic attribute clashes. You seem to be going with black as the background color even when that color is hardly present. Oil Ocean would probably look much better if you used orange as the background color, so you could draw all the little ornaments without all the attribute clash.<br /><br />As for Emerald Hill, the black under the grass can almost be overlooked, but the light blue going into the sky is unacceptable. I'd much rather have the sky and the water use the same color, and be separated only by the surface of the water.

		

